attributes.value: / Nicks is an example module for keeping track of account names on-chain. It makes no effort to
/ create a name hierarchy, be a DNS replacement or provide reverse lookups. Furthermore, the
/ weights attached to this module's dispatchable functions are for demonstration purposes only and
/ have not been designed to be economically secure. Do not use this pallet as-is in production.
/ * `set_name` - Set the associated name of an account; a small deposit is reserved if not already
/ * `clear_name` - Remove an account's associated name; the deposit is returned.
/ * `kill_name` - Forcibly remove the associated name; the deposit is lost.

pub enum Error<T: Config> {
    __Ignore(::frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<(T,)>,
             ::frame_support::Never),
    TooShort,

}

defs.name: set_name
defs.docs:
Set an account's name. The name should be a UTF-8-encoded string by convention, though
 we don't check it.

defs.name: clear_name
defs.docs: Clear an account's name and return the deposit. Fails if the account was not named.

defs.name: kill_name
defs.docs: Remove an account's name and take charge of the deposit.

defs.name: force_name
defs.docs: Set a third-party account's name with no deposit.

defs.name: Call
defs.value:
pub enum Call<T: Config> {
    __PhantomItem(::frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<(T,)>,
                  ::frame_support::Never),
    set_name(Vec<u8>),
    clear_name(),
    kill_name(<T::Lookup as StaticLookup>::Source),
    force_name(<T::Lookup as StaticLookup>::Source, Vec<u8>),
}
